  • java.lang.Object

    public final class MapValueComparator<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V>
extends Object
implements Comparator<K>
    MapValueComparator is a Comparator that allows sorting a Map's keys based on the values mapped to the keys.

    dkatzel

      • sortAscending

        public static <K extends Comparable<? super K>,V> SortedMap<K,V> sortAscending(Map<K,V> unsorted,
                                                                               Comparator<V> comparator)
        Create an unmodifiable SortedMap that is sorted by value in ascending order. If there are duplicate values, then their sort order will be determined by comparing the keys to each other also in ascending order.
        Type Parameters:
        K - The Comparable type of Key contained in the map.
        V - The type of the values contained in the map (does not have to be comparable).
        Parameters:
        unsorted - the unsorted Map to be sorted.
        comparator - the Comparator used to sort the values in this map.
        Returns:
        a sorted map sorted by the values in ascending order; never null.
